<h2>Getting Started</h2>
<p>Once the REF Support plugin is installed on your EPrints Repository, you must complete the following set-up tasks in order to utilise the REF Support features.</p>

<h3>Additional Roles</h3>
<p>Relevant repository user accounts will need additional roles assigned to be able to access the screens within the REF Support plugin. Assign the two roles below as described:</p>

<table class="roles">
        <tr>
                <th>ref/select_champions</th>
                <td>Required to be able to identify members of staff as Unit of Assessment Champions</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
                <th>ref/select</th>
                <td>Required against those accounts (including Unit of Assessment Champions) needing to be able to access REF screens and to make REF submissions</td>

        </tr>
</table>

<p>These additional roles can be added by Repository Administrators to appropriate user accounts, using the ‘Administer Account’ feature</p>

<h3>Identify Unit of Assessment Champions</h3>
<p>You must identify your Unit of Assessment (UoA) Champions who will then be able to oversee and verify submissions to their assigned assessment panels.</p>

<p>To assign someone as a UoA Champion, go to their user profile and click "<epc:phrase ref="Plugin/Screen/REF_Support/User/EditUoA:title"/>" (this will only appear if you have the 'ref/select_champions' role yourself).</p>

<h3>Assign staff to their unit of assessment and populate REF1 profile information</h3>
<p>You must identify the staff involved in REF2014 who will be submitting research outputs by assigning them to a single unit of assessment panel. Should you choose to use your EPrints repository to produce your REF1 report you will also need to update staff profiles with the relevant REF1 information.</p>

<h3>Create the first current benchmark</h3>
<p>You must have one current benchmark set up for staff and Unit of Assessment Champions to be able to make submissions against and run associated reports.</p>

<p>To create a benchmark, click the '<epc:phrase ref="Plugin/Screen/DataSets:title"/> link in the main menu, then select '<epc:phrase ref="datasetname_ref_support_benchmark"/>'.</p>

